d decision-making from the understanding of data relationships, ensuring that the knowledge can be used to make informed decisions and accurate forecasts. By comprehending and utilizing data relationships effectively, wisdom enables individuals to make sound decisions and correct predictions.", "\"CUSTOMER INTERACTIONS\":\"Customer interactions refer to the various ways in which a business engages with its customers, including communication through emails, phone calls, social media, and in-person meetings.\"", "\"CUSTOMER DATA\":\"Customer data includes any information related to customers, such as contact details, purchase history, preferences, and feedback.\"", "\"CUSTOMER SERVICE\":Customer service involves assisting and supporting customers before, during, and after a purchase to ensure a positive experience and satisfaction. It encompasses the assistance and advice provided by a company to those who buy or use its products or services. Customer service is vital in service industries and also critical in manufacturing industries.", "\"CUSTOMER RETENTION\":\"Customer retention refers to the strategies and actions a business takes to keep its existing customers and reduce customer churn.\"", "\"SALES GROWTH\":\"Sales growth\" refers to the increase in sales over a specific period, often measured as a percentage increase from one period to the next. In a specific example, overall sales growth was calculated as $238,500/$200,000, resulting in a +19.25% increase. However, it is noted that sales in the female hairdressing sector have fallen by 15%, calculated as ($200,000 - $170,000)/$200,000.", "\"USER SUPPORT\":\"User support refers to the assistance provided to users of a system or software, including help desks, tutorials, and customer service.\"", "\"REPORTING FEATURES\":\"Reporting features in a CRM system allow users to generate reports on various metrics, such as sales performance, customer interactions, and service efficiency.\"", "\"TRACKING FEATURES\":\"Tracking features in a CRM system enable the monitoring of customer interactions, sales activities, and service requests to ensure timely follow-ups and resolution.\"", "\"DATA MODEL\":\"A data model is a conceptual representation of the data structures that are required for a database and is used to define how data is connected and how it is processed and stored.\"", "\"DATA PROCESSING\":\"Data processing involves the collection, manipulation, and transformation of data to extract meaningful information and insights.\"", "\"MACHINE LEARNING TECHNIQUES\":\"Machine learning techniques involve algorithms and statistical models that enable computers to perform tasks without explicit instructions, by relying on patterns and inference.\"", "\"VOICE ANALYTICS\":\"Voice analytics involves analyzing audio data to extract useful information, such as keywords and sentiment, similar to text analytics but with spoken language.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}